\section{Background}{

The \emph{Cocktail} method (Bruelheide 2000, 2016) merges species into groups based on the
\strong{phi coefficient of association}. Each cluster is characterised by its member species
and a membership threshold (\emph{m}) indicating how many cluster species a plot must contain
to belong to that node.
